|url=https://archive.org/details/perspectivesonka00thom/page/191 }}\n* {{citation |last=Zutshi |first=Chitralekha |title=Languages of Belonging: Islam, Regional Identity, and the Making of Kashmir |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dlBjzE-1ML8C |publisher=C. Hurst & Co. Publishers |isbn=978-1-85065-700-2 |ref={{sfnref|Zutshi, Languages of Belonging|2004}}|year=2004 }}\n*{{citation|first1=Ian|last1=Talbot|first2=Gurharpal|last2=Singh|title=The Partition of India|year=2009|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-85661-4|ref={{sfnref|Talbot & Singh, The Partition of India|2009}}}}\n*{{citation|first=Gurharpal|last=Singh|title=Ethnic Conflict in India: A Case Study of Punjab|year=2000|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan UK|isbn=978-0-333-98177-1|ref={{sfnref|Singh, Ethnic Conflict in India|2000}}}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin}}\n\n=== Pre-independence history===\n* Drew, Federic. 1877. ''The Northern Barrier of India: a popular account of the Jammoo and Kashmir Territories with Illustrations''.&;#8221; 1st edition: Edward Stanford, London. Reprint: Light & Life Publishers, Jammu. 1971.\n\n=== Partition and post-independence===\n* Webb, Matthew J. ''Kashmir's right to secede: A critical examination of contemporary theories of secession''. Vol. 54. Routledge, 2012\n* Howard B. Schaffer [https://books.google.com/books?id=3Stqszkd0RwC&pg=PA103 ''Chester Bowles: New Dealer in the Cold War'']. Harvard University Press. 1993 {{ISBN|978-0-674-11390-9}}.\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Bradnock | first1 = Robert W | year = 1998 | title = Regional geopolitics in a globalising world: Kashmir in geopolitical perspective | url = | journal = Geopolitics | volume = 3 | issue = 2| pages = 1\u201329 | doi=10.1080/14650049808407617}}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Heymann | first1 = Karen | year = 2003 | title = Earned Sovereignty for Kashmir: The Legal Methodology to Avoiding a Nuclear Holocaust | url = | journal = Am. U. Int'l L. Rev. | volume = 19 | issue = | page